description: Nonprime numbers n such that n remains nonprime if any digit deleted (zeros not allowed in n).
links: T. D. Noe and Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000, first 1000 terms by T. D. Noe
prog: (Haskell)a034305 n = a034305_list !! (n-1)a034305_list = filter f $ drop 9 a052382_list where  f x = a010051' x == 0 &&        (all (== 0) $ map (a010051' . read) $         zipWith (++) (inits $ show x) (tail $ tails $ show x))-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, May 10 2015
author: _David W. Wilson_
extensions: Definition corrected by T. D. Noe, Apr 02 2008
